@node cookies "Cookies for the replyheaders"

*** List of '%' cookies for replyheaders ***

    \n - newline

    %F - the sender of the quoted message.
    %f - the first name of the sender of the quoted message.
    %n - the nodenumber of the sender of the quoted message.

    %T - the recipient of the quoted message.
    %t - the first name of the recipient of the quoted message.

    %S - the subject of the quoted message.

    %D - the date the quoted message was written, in MM-DDD-YY format.
    %U - the time the quoted message was written, in HH:MM:SS format.

    %A - the name of the messagearea the quoted message was written in.
    %a - the tagname of the messagearea the quoted message was written in.
@endnode
@node magicfile_commercial "MagicFile Advertisement - (c) Manuel Groeneweg"

                              @{b}MagicFile v1.71@{ub}
             A full-screen ANSI file tagger for Xenolink 1.98+

               The first and ONLY file-tagger for Xenolink!

                 Copyright © 1994-1996 by Manuel Groeneweg
                            All rights reserved

                                   -----

 o Supports the following files:
     - Xenolinks standard file catalog
     - external configs (for CD-ROMS)
     - Aminet FILES.BBS
     - Gifs Galore 00_INDEX.TXT
     - Users private dir (from UserFileBox)

 o Optional buffering of CD-ROM files for systems with CD-ROM changers.

 o Supports external doors (with possible access restrictions) for eg.:
     - Downloading
     - Archive viewing
     - Long descriptions
     - File maintenance/editing
     - Anything you can write yourself

 o All text strings configurable
 o All keys configurable
 o All colors configurable
 o Online help through text file
 o Lots more, see for yourself!

                                   -----

@endnode
@node config_starteditorcommand "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} STARTEDITORCOMMAND <command> [AUTO]


@{i}Example:@{ui}

STARTEDITORCOMMAND  "C:CED t:message.tmp -sticky"  AUTO


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the command MagicEditor will use to run the editor. If you
       leave the AUTO switch out the editor will not automatically run at
       startup.

@endnode
@node config_crossreplyheader "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} CROSSREPLYHEADER <header>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

CROSSREPLYHEADER  "** Cross-reply from '%A'"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} Click @{"here" link cookies} for a list of cookies you can use.
@endnode
@node config_defaultreplyheader "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DEFAULTREPLYHEADER <header>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

DEFAULTREPLYHEADER  "%F wrote a message to %T about '%S'"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} Click @{"here" link cookies} for a list of cookies you can use.
@endnode
@node config_replyheader "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} REPLYHEADER <message_area_range> <header>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

REPLYHEADER  100-120  "%F wrote about '%S'"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} Click @{"here" link cookies} for a list of cookies you can use.
@endnode
@node config_defaultsignaturenormal "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DEFAULTSIGNATURENORMAL <signaturefile>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

DEFAULTSIGNATURENORMAL  Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature


@{i}Notes:@{ui} 
@endnode
@node config_defaultsignaturehandle "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DEFAULTSIGNATUREHANDLE <signaturefile>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

DEFAULTSIGNATUREHANDLE  Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature.handle


@{i}Notes:@{ui} 
@endnode
@node config_signature "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} SIGNATURE <message_area_range> <signaturefile>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

SIGNATURE  15-25,300-400  Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature.fido


@{i}Notes:@{ui} 
@endnode
@node config_defaulttagline "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DEFAULTTAGLINE <taglinefile>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

DEFAULTTAGLINE  Doors:MagicEditor/taglines/MagicEditor.taglines


@{i}Notes:@{ui} 
@endnode
@node config_tagline "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} TAGLINE <message_area_range> <taglinefile>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

TAGLINE  0,50-81,100-118  Doors:MagicEditor/taglines/taglines.nl


@{i}Notes:@{ui} You can have as much TAGLINE lines in your config as your memory permits.
@endnode
@node config_defaultcharset "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DEFAULTCHARSET <charsetstring>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

DEFAULTCHARSET  "LATIN-1 2"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} 
@endnode
@node config_charset "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} CHARSET <message_area_range> <charsetstring>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

CHARSET  25,26  "IBMPC 1"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} You can have as much CHARSET lines in your config as your memory permits.
@endnode
